definitions.definition: Of an organic compound: having a closed ring of more than about twelve atoms .
Of or relating to a macrocycle .
Pertaining to a rust fungus whose life cycle includes all five spore stages: pycniospore ( spermatium ), aeciospore , urediniospore , teliospore , and basidiospore .

main_definition: ( chemistry ) Of an organic compound: having a closed ring of more than about twelve atoms .
